  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nSome extra features to improve `lcli` since we are using it in (under development) new beacon-fuzz tool.\r\n\r\n### First feature\r\n\r\nWhen you provide bad stuff to `lcli` you will get something like that as output\r\n```\r\n./shared/lighthouse/lcli --spec mainnet transition-blocks pre.ssz block.ssz\r\n2020-05-01 15:34:27,943 INFO  [lcli::transition_blocks] Using minimal spec\r\n2020-05-01 15:34:27,943 INFO  [lcli::transition_blocks] Pre-state path: \"pre.ssz\"\r\n2020-05-01 15:34:27,943 INFO  [lcli::transition_blocks] Block path: \"block.ssz\"\r\nFailed to run lcli: Failed to transition blocks: Ssz decode failed: OffsetIntoFixedPortion(1)\r\n```\r\nAll logs are written using stdout and it will be good to have the error message `Failed to run lcli: Failed to transition blocks: Ssz decode failed: OffsetIntoFixedPortion(1))` printed using stderr\r\n\r\n### 2nd feature\r\n\r\n`lcli` have a pretty-hex subcommand and it will be nice to have a simple pretty subcommand taking a type and a file name/path\r\n",
